{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7c5f45fd-9363-4bb1-9f3f-e03a95c3991a","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update packages** in your `.csproj`:\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n   - Update `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support)\n   - Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` if you need TRX output\n\n2. **Add a property** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly via the built executable (`dotnet run`).\n\n4. **Optional** — generate an entry point automatically by adding:\n   ```xml\n   <GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n   ```\n   (enabled by default with NUnit3TestAdapter 5.x).\n\n**Key behavioral differences to watch for:**\n- Each test project now produces a **standalone executable** with its own test runner.\n- `--filter` syntax remains the same, but some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options may not carry over.\n- Extensions (loggers, reporters) are now registered via NuGet packages (e.g., `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.*`) rather than VSTest adapters.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9e618087-4e9b-4fa4-99be-ce24c04be655","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure - I don't need to look at any code. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":416,"requestId":"982F:254503:1622D2:1D281F:69FFD7C3"},"id":"b3a5af71-a643-4992-bf4e-753029f62608","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:56:45.809Z","parentId":"bb6a6a01-7d14-4e8a-a955-4089ff463505"}
